The White House Office of National Drug Control Policy (ONDCP) and the United States Anti-Doping Agency recently held a meeting at the White House to discuss the need for reform in the World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA). Representatives from various countries and the global athletic community attended the meeting. They expressed their support for athlete-centered reform of the WADA-led anti-doping system. The goal is to ensure a strong domestic and global anti-doping program, allowing young people worldwide to experience the benefits of clean competition. The attendees called for WADA to provide stronger leadership in promoting clean competition.